<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
        <title><%= title %></title>
        <%- include('shared-css'); -%>
        <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/index.css' />
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-1"></div>
                <div class="col-md-10 position-relative" style="height: 100vh">
                    <div class="landing-page text-center">
                        <h1 class="logo">Reminder.ai</h1>
                        <p class="intro">Set up reminders with progress alerts between each start and due date.</p>
                        <!-- Collapse buttons -->
                        <div class="tab-group">
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary waves-effect js-tab" data-target="#progressAlert">Progress Alerts</button>
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary waves-effect js-tab" data-target="#visualElements">Visual Elements</button>
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary waves-effect js-tab" data-target="#emailNotifications">Email Notifications</button>
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary waves-effect js-tab" data-target="#speechRecognition">Speech Recognition</button>
                        </div>
                        <!-- / Collapse buttons -->
                        <!-- Collapsible element -->
                        <div class="collapse feature-description" id="progressAlert">
                            <div class="mx-5 mb-3 mt-3 d-inline-block">
                                <p>With Reminder.ai, you can set time-progress notifications for reminders between their start and a due dates.</p>
                                <p>This way, your due dates will never catch you by surprise.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse feature-description" id="visualElements">
                            <div class="mx-5 mb-5 mt-3 d-inline-block">
                                <p>In Reminder.ai, reminders have different colors to indicate their time progress and urgency.</p>
                                <p class="red-status"> > 95% time lapsed </p>
                                <p class="yellow-status"> > 70% time lapsed </p>
                                <p class="white-status"> < 70% time lapsed </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse feature-description" id="emailNotifications">
                            <div class="mx-5 mb-3 mt-3 d-inline-block">
                                <p>Besides getting in-app notifications, you can set your notifications to send straight to your email.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse feature-description" id="speechRecognition">
                            <div class="mx-5 mb-3 mt-3 d-inline-block">
                                <p>With Reminder.ai, you may set up reminders faster just by saying it - It will recognize what you're saying..</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- / Collapsible element -->
                        <a href="/dashboard"><button type="button" class="btn btn-light-blue">Start now -></button></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-1"></div>
            </div>
            <video autoplay muted loop id="bg-video">
                <source src="/videos/reminder-ai-bg.mp4" type="video/mp4">
            </video>
        </div>
        <%- include('shared-js'); -%>
        <script>
            $('.collapse').collapse('hide');
            $('.js-tab').click(function(e){
            e.preventDefault();
            $('.collapse').collapse('hide');
            $($(this).data('target')).collapse('show');
            })
        </script>
    </body>
</html>
